# BR2-AI-Beast

A reinforcement learning agent that learns to play **Bloody Roar 2** on the DuckStation PS1 emulator.
It uses Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) via Stable-Baselines3, training directly from raw screen captures.

## How it works

```
Windows (DuckStation)              Windows (Python)
┌─────────────────┐   frames       ┌──────────────────────┐
│  DuckStation    │ ─────────────► │  training/server.py  │
│  (PS1 emulator) │                │  (FastAPI + PPO)     │
└─────────────────┘ ◄───────────── └──────────────────────┘
                      button cmds
```

1. **Capture client** (`capture/ws_client.py`) grabs frames from the DuckStation window using DXGI, compresses them as JPEG, and streams them over a WebSocket.
2. **Inference server** (`training/main.py`) receives frames, preprocesses them (resize → grayscale → normalize), stacks 4 frames for temporal context, and runs the PPO agent to select an action.
3. Actions are sent back as JSON and the client presses the corresponding buttons via a virtual Xbox 360 controller (ViGEm / vgamepad).

## Project structure

```
br2-ai-beast/
├── capture/
│   ├── capture.py       # DuckStation window capture (dxcam, Windows only)
│   └── ws_client.py     # WebSocket client — streams frames, executes actions
├── training/
│   ├── main.py          # Entry point: --mode inference | train
│   ├── server.py        # FastAPI WebSocket inference server
│   ├── agent.py         # BR2Agent wrapper around SB3 PPO
│   ├── env.py           # Gymnasium environment for training loop
│   ├── train.py         # PPO training loop
│   ├── vision.py        # Frame decode, preprocess, FrameStacker
│   └── actions.py       # Discrete action set (18 actions)
├── controller.py        # VirtualController — maps actions to vgamepad inputs
├── conftest.py          # Adds project root to sys.path for pytest
├── run.ps1              # Single-command launcher (see below)
└── environment.yml      # Conda environment definition
```

## Setup

```powershell
conda env create -f environment.yml
conda activate br2-ai
```

> Requires Windows with ViGEm Bus Driver installed for virtual controller support.
> See: https://github.com/nefarius/ViGEmBus/releases

Copy `.env.sample` to `.env` and fill in your values:

```
DUCKSTATION_WINDOW_TITLE=<exact window title of DuckStation>
WS_HOST=0.0.0.0
WS_PORT=8765
```

## Running

### Inference (play with a trained model)

```powershell
.\run.ps1
.\run.ps1 -Control          # enable virtual controller input
.\run.ps1 -Model models/ppo_br2.zip -Control
```

This starts the inference server in a new window, waits for it to be ready, then launches the capture client.

### Training

```powershell
.\run.ps1 -Mode train
.\run.ps1 -Mode train -Timesteps 2000000
.\run.ps1 -Mode train -Model models/checkpoint.zip -Timesteps 1000000
```

### Run scripts directly

```powershell
# Server only
python -m training.main --mode inference --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8765

# Client only (server must already be running)
python -m capture.ws_client --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8765
```

## Tests

```powershell
pytest
```
